OL,3,CNurse jailed for murder of elderly
OL,4,Cpatients in Leeds loses conviction
OL,5,Cappeals
OL,7,FThey were inpatients on orthopaedic
OL,8,Fwards where Campbell worked in Leeds
OL,9,Fin 2002 before they died, and had
OL,10,Fdeveloped severe, unexplained
OL,11,Fhypoglycaemia.
OL,13,FCampbell denied any wrongdoing and
OL,14,Fsaid he did nothing to cause
OL,15,Fhypoglycaemia in any of the patients.
OL,17,FHis case was referred to the Court of
OL,18,FAppeal in London by the Criminal Cases
OL,19,FReview Commission in 2021, who said
OL,20,Fpreviously that the prosecution relied
OL,21,Fon "wholly circumstantial" evidence.
